{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pizza dough","content":["Lightly grease a large bowl and set aside. Place water, sugar or malt powder (optional) and yeast into mixing bowl and mix <nobr>20 sec\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add baker's flour, extra virgin olive oil and salt and knead <nobr>2 min\/<\/nobr>. Place dough into prepared bowl and form into a ball. Cover bowl with plastic wrap or a damp kitchen towel and leave dough to prove until doubled in size (approx. 1 hour)."]},{"title":"Margherita topping","content":["Preheat oven to 220°C. Line 2 large baking trays with baking paper or grease with extra virgin olive oil and set aside.","Place mozzarella into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. If using 'wet' mozzarella, such as bocconcini, transfer into simmering basket and leave to drain for 10 minutes.","Divide dough into 2 balls. Place dough on prepared baking trays and shape into a rectangle the size of the baking tray by pressing it with your finger tips and stretching it gently. Form a small ridge around the edges.","Spread chopped tomatoes and mozzarella on top of dough and sprinkle with salt, olive oil and 5-7 torn basil leaves.Bake pizzas for 20 minutes (220°C). Scatter remaining torn basil leaves over pizza and serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pizza dough","content":["30 g extra virgin olive oil, plus extra for greasing","220 g water, room temperature","1 tsp sugar              (optional)","20 g fresh yeast, crumbled","400 g baker's flour, plus extra for dusting","1 tsp salt"]},{"title":"Margherita topping","content":["200 g mozzarella cheese, cut into pieces","250 g canned chopped tomatoes","¼ - ½ tsp salt, to taste","1 tbsp extra virgin olive oil","10 - 15 fresh basil leaves, torn into pieces"]}],"id":"r67444","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-_Sm4jRsPhK4\/XZWZAjwBy2I\/AAAAAAAAeGY\/XxcivYSJ1aYeIOXhr1BUZ7jLbGhja1WjwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RbpBAlvZSVhsmLp-.png","title":"Pizza Margherita","publishedAt":"2014-09-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"20 g","fat":"24 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"78 g","calories":"2544 kJ \/ 607 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, plastic wrap or kitchen towel, 2 baking trays and paper, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Add your favourite toppings (e.g. zucchini, olives, egg, cheese, fruit, herbs).","Alternatively, roll pizza dough out on a ThermoMat or floured work surface using a rolling pin, and transfer dough onto prepared baking tray.","4 smaller round pizzas can be made from the dough. For extra crispy results, try baking one pizza at a time and sharing each as it comes out fresh from the oven.","In step 2 the plastic wrap can be lightly oiled to prevent it from sticking to the proving dough.","If mozzarella is dry there is no need to drain it.","If chopped tomatoes have a lot of liquid, drain through simmering basket before using."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","2h 10m","4 pieces"]}